%BOM---------------------
Date:3/20/2011 12:46:08 PM
From:ValueGuy
All good points and have to agree with all of them.

I guess what I'm trying to say is that just because we expect an auditor to do
his job, does not mean that he is doing his job, especially in 'basic' areas
such as bank and cash or PPE.

Just because someone says the market is efficient, does not mean that the
market is efficient. Same thing with auditors. Most financial statements with
an unqualified opinion deserves that tag (I mean, what else would we rely on
right?), but once in a while you will get things missed (either by error or
deliberate), especially if they are not deemed material or if the auditor has a
really 'good' relationship with his client.
