It's amazing how JNJ BOD finds great reasons to pay CEO $29M while the company
continues to fumble through quality issues and recalls destroying its brand
cachet. What would it take for them to reduce the bonuses? CEO announcing that
the company would reduce drug prices for the poor? Yeah, probably that's the
ticket.

Anyway I voted against executive compensation so far for every company not
counting BRK and FRFHF. Hmm, I'm not sure FRFHF asked to vote on executive
compensation, but I would have voted for it. Fairfax chairman's letter is worth
reading ( http://www.fairfax.ca/financial.htm ) even if he channels Buffett a
bit.

So vote early and vote often.
